Amer Group and Ezz Steel: Egyptian Equity Preview

-- B y   A h m e d   A .   N a m a t a l l a
-- 
2011-09-14T08:03:09Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-14/amer-group-and-ezz-steel-egyptian-equity-preview.html
The following companies may be
active in  Egypt ’s stock market. Symbols are in parentheses and
prices are from last close.  The benchmark EGX30 Index dropped 1.6 percent to 4,538.58
in Cairo.  Amer Group (AMER EY): Egypt’s tourist arrivals in August
were down 21 percent from a year earlier, the Ministry of
Tourism said in a statement yesterday. Shares of the Cairo-based
resorts and restaurants developer and operator declined 3.1
percent to 1.26 Egyptian pounds.  Ezz Steel (ESRS)  : Egypt’s biggest manufacturer of the
metal had its share-price estimate cut 9 percent to 11 Egyptian
pounds at EFG-Hermes Holding SAE because of the Arab country’s
recent tax hike, higher labor costs and delays to the start of a
new plant. The investment bank’s recommendation on the stock was
maintained at “buy.” The shares lost 2.7 percent to 8.42
pounds.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ahmed A Namatalla in Cairo at 
 anamatalla@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
